{%- comment -%}
  Header cart icon — dedicated section used ONLY as a Section Rendering
  API target from `assets/cart-drawer.js::refreshDrawer()`.

  Why a standalone section: the drawer's refreshDrawer fetches
  `/?sections=cart-drawer,header-cart-icon` after every qty change or
  ATC. The Section Rendering API requires the `sections` key to
  reference real section files; without this file the `header-cart-icon`
  response key was silently missing and the drawer fell through to a
  full cart.js fetch, round-tripping extra bytes on every update.

  The cart count pill that visually lives in sections/header.liquid is
  duplicated here — the JS swaps the inner textContent, not the node,
  so the visible header icon (rendered by sections/header.liquid) keeps
  its event listeners intact. Keeping this section tiny keeps the SRA
  response small (~200 bytes vs. the ~5 KB header.liquid would emit).

  NOT rendered on the storefront — it isn't in any template's section
  group. Shopify's SRA accepts orphan sections as long as the section
  file exists, which is the entire purpose here.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  R298 — `aria-live` REMOVED here too. This is the Section Rendering
  API fragment used for AJAX cart-count refreshes. If a future
  regression mounts it into the live DOM alongside the canonical
  header.liquid badge, two `aria-live` regions racing would
  double-announce. `Kitchero.announce()` is the single source of
  truth for cart-change announcements.
{%- endcomment -%}
<span
  class="kt-header__cart-count"
  data-section-id="{{ section.id }}"
  aria-hidden="{% if cart.item_count == 0 %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}"
  {% if cart.item_count == 0 %}style="display: none;"{% endif %}
>
  {{ cart.item_count }}
</span>

{%- comment -%}
  R98 — `disabled_on: { groups: ["*"], templates: ["*"] }` previously
  blocked Shopify's Section Rendering API from invoking this section's
  Liquid render path. cart-drawer.js POSTs add-to-cart, then GETs
  `/?sections=cart-drawer,header-cart-icon` to swap the rendered
  fragments back in. With the wildcard disable in place, the SRA
  response returned an empty body for the `header-cart-icon` key — so
  the count badge in the live header silently stopped updating after
  any add/remove. (Same Shopify-side pitfall documented in
  predictive-search.liquid:10-19.) The section is still hidden from
  the editor's "Add section" picker because it has no `presets` array
  — Shopify only surfaces sections with at least one preset entry.
{%- endcomment -%}
{% schema %}
{
  "name": "t:sections.header-cart-icon.name",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
